Example URL:
http://codepen.io/jedierikb/pen/ZGqdvN?editors=101

Steps to reproduce the problem:
Make a canvas element width=100 height=131.

var $c = document.getElementById("c");
var ctx = $c.getContext("2d");
ctx.fillStyle = "rgba(255,0,0,1)";
ctx.beginPath();
ctx.lineTo(69.7030518991886, 0);
ctx.bezierCurveTo( 69.7030518991886, 21.831149999999997, 58.08369508178456, 43.66448333333333, 34.8449814469765, 65.5);
ctx.bezierCurveTo( 11.608591683531916, 87.33115, -0.010765133872116195, 109.16448333333332, -0.013089005235602302, 131);
ctx.closePath();
ctx.fill();

What is the expected behavior?
Should draw a nice curvy shape.

What went wrong?
Instead of a curvy shape, a blocky corner is drawn on our otherwise svelte shape.

Does it occur on multiple sites: Yes

Is it a problem with a plugin? No 

Did this work before? Yes 3-4 months ago?

Does this work in other browsers? Yes 

Chrome version: 44.0.2403.107  Channel: stable
OS Version: OS X 10.10.4
Flash Version: Shockwave Flash 18.0 r0

This painting can be "fixed" by painting on a different size canvas (e.g. width=100 height=121 instead of width=100 height=131)

