fukino@, yoshiki@, mtomasz@: this seems to be a timing sensitive bug in the video player. The UI glitch is actually the <div id="thumbnail"> blended on top of the <div id="video_container">.

In ui/file_manager/video_player/js/video_player.js we invoke media.getThumbnail() and update the <div id="thumbnail"> in the callback:

    Promise.all([media.getThumbnail(), media.getToken(false)])
        .then(function(results) {
          var url = results[0];
          var token = results[1];
          if (url && token) {
            queryRequiredElement(document, '#thumbnail').style.backgroundImage =      // <==== PROBLEM
                'url(' + url + '&access_token=' + token + ')';
          } else {
            queryRequiredElement(document, '#thumbnail').style.backgroundImage =
                '';
          }
        })
        .catch(function() {
          // Shows no image on error.
          queryRequiredElement(document, '#thumbnail').style.backgroundImage =
              '';
        });

The problem here is that the media.getThumbnail() can take a non-trivial amount of time (our recent migration of Sandybridge devices to freon has possibly increased that time) to reach the callback. The time it takes is longer when playing back content on Google Drive. Anyway we somehow ended up in a state where both the thumbnail and the video container are blended together.

If I manually modify video_player.js and force "#thumbnail".style.backgroundImage = '' then there is no glitch.
